answer.en:
### Custom Hook for Form State

Controlled inputs have their value managed by React state, allowing real-time validation and easier data handling. Custom hooks encapsulate form logic for reusability. Uncontrolled inputs rely on the DOM, making validation and synchronization harder.

```typescript
function useForm(initialValues) {
  const [values, setValues] = useState(initialValues);
  const [errors, setErrors] = useState({});

  const handleChange = (e) => {
    const { name, value } = e.target;
    setValues(prev => ({ ...prev, [name]: value }));
  };

  return { values, handleChange, errors, setErrors };
}
```

**Common interview trap:** Mixing controlled and uncontrolled inputs in the same form creates unpredictable behavior.

answer.ru:
