### Custom Renderers

React Core is platform-agnostic; renderers implement platform-specific logic through the reconciler interface. Renderers handle creating/updating/removing host instances (DOM nodes, native views). You can create custom renderers using createRoot and the reconciler package (react-reconciler).

```typescript
// Simplified custom renderer example
import { Reconciler } from 'react-reconciler';

const reconciler = Reconciler({
  createInstance(type, props, rootContainer) {
    return { type, props, children: [] };
  },
  appendChild(parentInstance, childInstance) {
    parentInstance.children.push(childInstance);
  },
  commitUpdate(instance, updatePayload) {
    Object.assign(instance.props, updatePayload);
  }
});
```

**Common interview trap:** Thinking React Core includes DOM logic; it doesn't.

