}

// С React Forget - автоматическая (концептуально)
function Component({ data }) {
  const memoizedValue = expensiveCompute(data); // Автомемоизация
  const memoizedCallback = () => handleClick(); // Автомемоизация
  return <Child value={memoizedValue} onClick={memoizedCallback} />;
}
```

**Типичная ошибка:** Предположение, что React Forget сразу заменит все useMemo.

answer.en:
### Server Components vs Traditional SSR

Server Components execute only on the server and never send their code to the client, reducing bundle size. They serialize to a special wire format instead of HTML, allowing seamless Server/Client boundaries. Traditional SSR hydrates HTML, requiring full component code client-side.

```typescript
// Server Component - never reaches client
'use server';
export default async function ServerOnly() {
  const data = await db.query();
  return <div>{data}</div>; // No JS sent
}

// Client Component needs full code
'use client';
export default function Interactive() {
  const [count, setCount] = useState(0);
  return <button onClick={() => setCount(c => c + 1)}>{count}</button>;
}
```

**Common interview trap:** Confusing Server Components with SSR—Server Components don't send HTML, they send serialized component trees.

