answer.en:
### React Forget (React Compiler)

React Forget automatically memoizes component outputs and dependencies without manual useMemo/useCallback, eliminating unnecessary re-renders. It analyzes data flow to identify values that don't change and wraps them in automatic memoization, transforming components into optimized versions at compile time.

```typescript
// Before: Manual memoization required
const MyComponent = ({ userId }) => {
  const user = useMemo(() => fetchUser(userId), [userId]);
  const handleClick = useCallback(() => console.log(user), [user]);
  return <button onClick={handleClick}>Click</button>;
};

// After: React Forget automatically optimizes
const MyComponent = ({ userId }) => {
  const user = fetchUser(userId); // Automatically memoized
  const handleClick = () => console.log(user); // Automatically stable
  return <button onClick={handleClick}>Click</button>;
};
```

**Common interview trap:** Thinking React Forget replaces all performance tuning—it only handles component-level memoization; algorithmic improvements and data fetching patterns still matter.

